[2026-03-13T17:38:19Z] [llm] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01SFCNbmWfkmo42kkvEdAuWE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01UufoeYvqvAwwALDBfu6oEn","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/USAGE.md","limit":200},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3424,"cache_read_input_tokens":43743,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3424,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_0174MVnqQzdA1TA2bgz29vUa","session_id":"1b08d49b-02d1-4c4d-80e7-fef14e91a7aa","uuid":"8c8a29f2-00fa-476a-9a00-1d322f92e8a9"}
[2026-03-13T17:38:19Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UufoeYvqvAwwALDBfu6oEn","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Cloche Usage\n     2→\n     3→Cloche runs containerized workflows for autonomous coding agents. You define a\n     4→workflow graph in the `.cloche` DSL, Cloche copies your project into a Docker\n     5→container, runs the workflow steps (agent prompts and shell scripts), and extracts\n     6→results to a git branch.\n     7→\n     8→## Core Concepts\n     9→\n    10→- **Workflow**: A directed graph of steps connected by named-result wiring.\n    11→- **Step**: A unit of work. Type is inferred: `prompt` = agent step, `run` = script step, `workflow_name` = workflow step (host only).\n    12→- **Result**: A named outcome reported by a step (e.g. `success`, `fail`, `needs-research`). Steps declare their possible results; the engine follows wiring based on the reported result.\n    13→- **Wiring**: Maps `step:result` pairs to the next step. Separate from step definitions.\n    14→- **Terminals**: `done` (success) and `abort` (failure) are built-in terminal targets.\n    15→\n    16→## Workflow DSL\n    17→\n    18→Workflow files use the `.cloche` extension and live in `.cloche/`. The first step\n    19→declared is the entry point. Graphs are validated at parse time (all results wired,\n    20→no orphans, entry point exists).\n    21→\n    22→### Minimal Example\n    23→\n    24→```\n    25→workflow \"develop\" {\n    26→  step implement {\n    27→    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    28→    results = [success, fail]\n    29→  }\n    30→\n    31→  step test {\n    32→    run = \"make test 2>&1\"\n    33→    results = [success, fail]\n    34→  }\n    35→\n    36→  implement:success -> test\n    37→  implement:fail -> abort\n    38→  test:success -> done\n    39→  test:fail -> abort\n    40→}\n    41→```\n    42→\n    43→### Step Configuration\n    44→\n    45→| Key | Type | Description |\n    46→|-----|------|-------------|\n    47→| `prompt` | string or `file(\"path\")` | Prompt template. Makes this an agent step. |\n    48→| `run` | string | Shell command. Makes this a script step. |\n    49→| `workflow_name` | string | Container workflow to dispatch. Makes this a workflow step (host only). |\n    50→| `results` | ident list | Declared result names, e.g. `[success, fail, give-up]`. |\n    51→| `max_attempts` | string | Max retries before automatic `give-up` result, e.g. `\"2\"`. |\n    52→| `timeout` | string | Step timeout as Go duration, e.g. `\"30m\"`, `\"2h\"`. Default: 30m. |\n    53→| `agent_command` | string | Agent binary name(s), comma-separated for fallback chains, e.g. `\"claude,gemini\"`. |\n    54→| `agent_args` | string | Override default agent arguments. |\n    55→| `feedback` | string | Set to `\"true\"` to include `.cloche/output/*.log` content in the prompt. |\n    56→| `prompt_step` | string | For workflow steps: which preceding step's output to use as the prompt. |\n    57→\n    58→A step must have exactly one of `prompt`, `run`, or `workflow_name`.\n    59→\n    60→### The `file()` Function\n    61→\n    62→`file(\"path\")` reads the file at the given path relative to the working directory\n    63→(`/workspace/` in containers) at execution time, not parse time. Use it for prompt\n    64→templates:\n    65→\n    66→```\n    67→prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    68→```\n    69→\n    70→### The `container {}` Block\n    71→\n    72→Can appear at step level or workflow level. Keys are stored with a `container.` prefix.\n    73→\n    74→**Step level** — per-step container config:\n    75→```\n    76→step code {\n    77→  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    78→  container {\n    79→    image         = \"custom-agent:v2\"\n    80→    memory        = \"4g\"\n    81→    network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\", \"api.example.com\"]\n    82→  }\n    83→  results = [success, fail]\n    84→}\n    85→```\n    86→\n    87→**Workflow level** — defaults for all steps:\n    88→```\n    89→workflow \"develop\" {\n    90→  container {\n    91→    agent_command = \"gemini\"\n    92→    image         = \"myregistry/myimage:v2\"\n    93→    memory        = \"4g\"\n    94→  }\n    95→  ...\n    96→}\n    97→```\n    98→\n    99→Supported keys: `image`, `memory`, `network_allow`, `agent_command`, `agent_args`.\n   100→\n   101→### The `host {}` Block\n   102→\n   103→Can appear at workflow level in host workflows (`.cloche/host.cloche`). Keys are stored\n   104→with a `host.` prefix. Configures agent defaults for agent steps running on the host.\n   105→\n   106→```\n   107→workflow \"main\" {\n   108→  host {\n   109→    agent_command = \"claude\"\n   110→  }\n   111→  ...\n   112→}\n   113→```\n   114→\n   115→Supported keys: `agent_command`, `agent_args`. Step-level `agent_command` and\n   116→`agent_args` config keys override the workflow-level `host {}` defaults.\n   117→\n   118→### Wiring Syntax\n   119→\n   120→Connect steps with `step:result -> next_step`:\n   121→\n   122→```\n   123→implement:success -> test\n   124→implement:fail -> abort\n   125→test:success -> done\n   126→test:fail -> fix\n   127→```\n   128→\n   129→### Wire Output Mappings\n   130→\n   131→Extract values from a step's JSON output and inject as env vars into the target:\n   132→\n   133→```\n   134→step-a:success -> step-b [ ENV_VAR = output.field, OTHER = output.list[0].name ]\n   135→```\n   136→\n   137→Path expressions:\n   138→\n   139→| Expression | Meaning |\n   140→|---|---|\n   141→| `output` | Raw output (full string) |\n   142→| `output.key` | JSON object field access |\n   143→| `output[N]` | JSON array index (0-based) |\n   144→| `output.a.b.c` | Deeply nested field access |\n   145→| `output.items[0].name` | Mixed field and index chaining |\n   146→\n   147→If the output is valid JSON, path expressions navigate the structure. If it's plain\n   148→text, only bare `output` works.\n   149→\n   150→### Retry Loops\n   151→\n   152→Wire failures back to earlier steps:\n   153→\n   154→```\n   155→test:fail -> fix\n   156→fix:success -> test    // retry the test\n   157→fix:fail -> abort\n   158→```\n   159→\n   160→Use `max_attempts` to cap retries. When exhausted, the step returns `give-up`:\n   161→\n   162→```\n   163→step fix {\n   164→  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/fix.md\")\n   165→  max_attempts = \"2\"\n   166→  results = [success, fail, give-up]\n   167→}\n   168→```\n   169→\n   170→### Parallel Branches (Fanout)\n   171→\n   172→Wire one result to multiple targets for concurrent execution:\n   173→\n   174→```\n   175→test:success -> lint\n   176→test:success -> quality\n   177→```\n   178→\n   179→### Collect (Join)\n   180→\n   181→Synchronize parallel branches:\n   182→\n   183→```\n   184→collect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n   185→collect any(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n   186→```\n   187→\n   188→`all` fires when every condition is met. `any` fires when at least one is.\n   189→\n   190→### Comments\n   191→\n   192→Line comments with `//`:\n   193→\n   194→```\n   195→// This is a comment\n   196→implement:success -> test  // inline comment\n   197→```\n   198→\n   199→## Result Protocol\n   200→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_0174MVnqQzdA1TA2bgz29vUa","session_id":"1b08d49b-02d1-4c4d-80e7-fef14e91a7aa","uuid":"986d7b3a-523a-48bf-9e09-4f996289abf3"}
