[2026-03-13T17:38:19Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0174MVnqQzdA1TA2bgz29vUa","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary of my findings.\n\n## Summary\n\nI've conducted a thorough search of the Cloche codebase and found extensive documentation and implementation for the three special host workflows: **list-tasks**, **main**, and **finalize**. Here's what I discovered:\n\n### Key Documentation Files\n\n**Primary Documentation:**\n- `/workspace/docs/workflows.md` - Complete DSL documentation with three-phase workflow section (lines 1-274)\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md` - Detailed design for host.cloche system\n- `/workspace/docs/USAGE.md` - User-facing documentation\n- `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-09-wire-output-mapping-design.md` - Wire output mappings for data flow between steps\n\n### The Three Workflows\n\n**1. list-tasks Workflow** (Phase 1)\n- Discovers available work by running a script\n- Output is parsed as **JSONL** (one JSON object per line)\n- Each task must have fields: `id`, `status`, `title`, `description`, `metadata`\n- Status values: `open`, `closed`, `in-progress` (or empty for backward compat)\n- Implementation: `/workspace/internal/host/task.go` - `ParseTasksJSONL()` and `ReadListTasksOutput()`\n- Optional: if absent, daemon uses legacy single-function mode\n\n**2. main Workflow** (Phase 2)\n- Executes the main work for a claimed task\n- Receives `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` environment variable\n- The task being processed is available in environment variables:\n  - `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`\n  - `CLOCHE_TASK_TITLE`\n  - `CLOCHE_TASK_BODY`\n- Must complete before finalize runs\n- Required: This is the only mandatory workflow\n\n**3. finalize Workflow** (Phase 3)\n- Post-main cleanup, runs on **both success and failure**\n- Receives outcome context via environment variables:\n  - `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` - \"succeeded\" or \"failed\"\n  - `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID` - ID of the main workflow run\n- Optional: skipped if absent\n- Implementation location: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` lines 901-924\n\n### Code Implementation Files\n\n**Core Host Workflow Execution:**\n- `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go` - `Runner` struct executes named workflows\n  - `Run()` / `RunWithID()` - execute main workflow\n  - `RunNamed()` - execute any named workflow\n  - `RunListTasksWorkflow()` - special handler for list-tasks with deduplication\n  \n- `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go` - `Executor` struct executes individual steps\n  - `executeScript()` - runs shell commands\n  - `executeWorkflow()` - dispatches container workflows via gRPC\n  - `executeAgent()` - runs agent on host\n  - `waitForRun()` - polls until container run completes\n\n- `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go` - Orchestration loop management\n  - `Loop` struct manages continuous orchestration\n  - `NewPhaseLoop()` - creates three-phase loop with list-tasks, main, finalize functions\n  - `runPhased()` - implements the phase orchestration (lines 174-271)\n  - `pickTaskFromPhase()` - selects next open task with deduplication (lines 309-351)\n  - Task deduplication prevents rapid reassignment within configurable timeout (default 5 min)\n\n- `/workspace/internal/host/task.go` - Task data structures\n  - `Task` struct with JSONL marshaling\n  - `TaskStatus` constants: `open`, `closed`, `in-progress`\n  - `IsOpen()` - checks if task is assignable\n  - `ParseTasksJSONL()` - parses JSONL task output\n  - `ReadListTasksOutput()` - reads most recent .out file from host run\n\n### Environment Variables for Host Workflows\n\nAll host steps receive:\n- `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` - Project directory path\n- `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` - Where step output should be written\n- `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` - Previous step's output file path\n- `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` - Current task ID (main phase and later)\n- `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` - Host run ID\n- Plus any wire output mappings\n\nFinalize phase additionally receives:\n- `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` - \"succeeded\" or \"failed\"\n- `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID` - Container run ID from main phase\n\n### Step Types in Host Workflows\n\nHost workflows support three step types (defined in `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`):\n1. **script** (`run` key) - Execute shell command\n2. **agent** (`prompt` key) - Invoke coding agent on host\n3. **workflow** (`workflow_name` key) - Dispatch container workflow, wait for completion\n   - Optional `prompt_step` config to override which step's output to use as prompt\n\n**Validation Rule:** `workflow_name` steps only allowed in host workflows (not container workflows) - enforced at parse time in `ValidateLocation()`\n\n### Actual Implementation in Cloche\n\n**Default host.cloche** (created by `cloche init`):\n- `/workspace/.cloche/host.cloche` - Actual project's orchestration workflow with three workflows:\n  - `list-tasks` - runs `/workspace/.cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh`\n  - `main` - multi-step: claim-task → prepare-prompt → develop → merge → cleanup\n  - `finalize` - runs close-task script\n\n**Associated Scripts:**\n- `/workspace/.cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh` - Lists available tasks\n- `/workspace/.cloche/scripts/claim-task.sh` - Claims a task\n- `/workspace/.cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh` - Generates prompt from task data\n- `/workspace/.cloche/scripts/merge-to-main.sh` - Merges completed work\n- `/workspace/.cloche/scripts/cleanup-run.sh` - Cleanup after run\n- `/workspace/.cloche/scripts/close-task.sh` - Closes task in tracker\n\n### DSL Parser\n\n**Parser function:** `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`\n- `ParseAllForHost()` at line 43 - parses host.cloche with multiple workflows\n- Infers `StepTypeWorkflow` when `workflow_name` key is present\n- Known config keys: `workflow_name`, `prompt_step` (in addition to `prompt`, `run`, etc.)\n\n### Orchestration Loop Phases\n\n**Phase Flow** (in `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go` `runPhased()` method):\n1. **Discover** - `listTasks()` → returns available tasks with dedup filtering\n2. **Assign** - picks first open task not recently assigned\n3. **Launch** - spins up goroutine for main+finalize pair\n4. **Main** - `mainFn()` executes main workflow with CLOCHE_TASK_ID\n5. **Finalize** - `finalizeFn()` executes finalize with outcome context (both success/failure)\n6. **Complete** - tracks run ID for task, continues filling to max_concurrent\n\n**Configuration:**\n- `MaxConcurrent` - concurrent runs per project\n- `StaggerDelay` - delay between consecutive launches\n- `DedupTimeout` - suppress reassignment window (default 5 min)\n\n### Important Design Patterns\n\n1. **Step Output Files** - Each step writes output to `.cloche/<run-id>/output/<step-name>.out`\n2. **Output Mappings** - Wire syntax: `step-a:success -> step-b [ KEY = output.field ]` extracts JSON fields\n3. **Main Worktree** - Host scripts execute from main git branch worktree (not linked worktrees)\n4. **Polling** - Container runs are polled with 2-second intervals until terminal state\n5. **Run Records** - Host runs tracked in store with `IsHost = true` flag\n6. **Task Deduplication** - Prevents same task from being picked again within timeout window\n\n### Git History\n\nKey commits related to this feature:\n- `3ab35fb` - Split host.cloche into three-phase loop\n- `824bd5f` - Update USAGE.md with three-phase workflow model\n\nAll files are production-ready with comprehensive implementation, testing, and documentation."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a0d58d07d5e793475 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 61805\ntool_uses: 32\nduration_ms: 49487</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1b08d49b-02d1-4c4d-80e7-fef14e91a7aa","uuid":"e0d3ea3c-cb5c-4e70-b277-b5380c012515","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand three special host workflows in the Cloche system: list-tasks, main, and finalize. Please find:\n\n1. All existing docume