[2026-03-13T17:40:09Z] [llm] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01WpwXucoirfkRuC3B9tcgyB","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01KkHeB1M8GhbYhbuLeYHdJ1","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/agent-setup-codex.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":174,"cache_read_input_tokens":13891,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":174,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01KdpomNNxMjpXpWeCYGkLvY","session_id":"832f6df2-1a53-47c0-b762-a9ee0142818b","uuid":"6af01031-905e-47b8-90c3-fa6bd0ba5147"}
[2026-03-13T17:40:09Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KkHeB1M8GhbYhbuLeYHdJ1","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# How to Set Up Codex\n     2→\n     3→This guide covers configuring Cloche containers to use\n     4→[OpenAI Codex](https://platform.openai.com/docs) as the coding agent.\n     5→\n     6→## Prerequisites\n     7→\n     8→- A working Cloche installation ([Installation guide](INSTALL.md))\n     9→- An OpenAI API key with Codex access\n    10→\n    11→## How Authentication Works\n    12→\n    13→Unlike Claude Code, Codex authenticates via an API key rather than a local session.\n    14→You pass your OpenAI API key into containers using environment variables.\n    15→\n    16→## Dockerfile\n    17→\n    18→Your `.cloche/Dockerfile` must install the Codex CLI:\n    19→\n    20→```dockerfile\n    21→FROM cloche-base:latest\n    22→USER root\n    23→\n    24→# Install Node.js (required for Codex CLI)\n    25→RUN apt-get update \\\n    26→    && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends nodejs npm \\\n    27→    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*\n    28→\n    29→# Install Codex CLI\n    30→RUN npm install -g @openai/codex\n    31→\n    32→# Add your project's build dependencies here\n    33→# RUN apt-get install -y ...\n    34→\n    35→USER agent\n    36→```\n    37→\n    38→## Passing the API Key\n    39→\n    40→Set `OPENAI_API_KEY` using `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV` in the daemon's environment:\n    41→\n    42→```bash\n    43→export CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV=\"OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...\"\n    44→cloched &\n    45→```\n    46→\n    47→`CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV` accepts comma-separated `KEY=VALUE` pairs and injects them into\n    48→every container.\n    49→\n    50→## Workflow Configuration\n    51→\n    52→Set `agent_command` to `codex` at the workflow or step level:\n    53→\n    54→**Workflow level** (applies to all steps):\n    55→\n    56→```\n    57→workflow \"develop\" {\n    58→  container {\n    59→    agent_command = \"codex\"\n    60→  }\n    61→\n    62→  step implement {\n    63→    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    64→    results = [success, fail]\n    65→  }\n    66→\n    67→  implement:success -> done\n    68→  implement:fail -> abort\n    69→}\n    70→```\n    71→\n    72→**Step level** (per-step override):\n    73→\n    74→```\n    75→step implement {\n    76→  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    77→  agent_command = \"codex\"\n    78→  results = [success, fail]\n    79→}\n    80→```\n    81→\n    82→Codex is not a \"known\" agent in Cloche, so it receives the prompt on stdin with no\n    83→default arguments. Add `agent_args` if the Codex CLI needs specific flags:\n    84→\n    85→```\n    86→step implement {\n    87→  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    88→  agent_command = \"codex\"\n    89→  agent_args = \"--full-auto\"\n    90→  results = [success, fail]\n    91→}\n    92→```\n    93→\n    94→## Fallback Chains\n    95→\n    96→Use Codex as a fallback if Claude is unavailable:\n    97→\n    98→```\n    99→agent_command = \"claude,codex\"\n   100→```\n   101→\n   102→Or use Codex as the primary with Claude as fallback:\n   103→\n   104→```\n   105→agent_command = \"codex,claude\"\n   106→```\n   107→\n   108→See [Agent Command Resolution](USAGE.md#agent-command-resolution) for full fallback\n   109→semantics.\n   110→\n   111→## Verifying the Setup\n   112→\n   113→Run a quick test workflow:\n   114→\n   115→```bash\n   116→cloche run --workflow develop --prompt \"Print hello world\"\n   117→```\n   118→\n   119→Check logs to confirm Codex is executing:\n   120→\n   121→```bash\n   122→cloche logs <run-id>\n   123→```\n   124→\n   125→## Troubleshooting\n   126→\n   127→**Codex not found in container**: Make sure your Dockerfile installs `@openai/codex`\n   128→via npm and that Node.js is available.\n   129→\n   130→**Authentication errors**: Verify that `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV` includes a valid\n   131→`OPENAI_API_KEY`. You can check by inspecting the container's environment:\n   132→\n   133→```bash\n   134→docker exec <container-id> env | grep OPENAI\n   135→```\n   136→\n   137→**No output from Codex**: Since Codex is not a known agent, Cloche passes the prompt\n   138→on stdin. Ensure the Codex CLI version you installed supports reading prompts from\n   139→stdin, or set appropriate `agent_args`.\n   140→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01KdpomNNxMjpXpWeCYGkLvY","session_id":"832f6df2-1a53-47c0-b762-a9ee0142818b","uuid":"6d6d81ea-3873-4da7-b8e8-9607dd7d148a"}
