dling\n- Prompt hygiene\n- Review before merge\n- Summary table of risks and mitigations\n\n### 5. **docs/agent-setup-claude.md** (Full contents)\n\nSetup guide for Claude Code including:\n\n- Prerequisites\n- How authentication works (copying `~/.claude/` and `~/.claude.json`)\n- Dockerfile requirements (Node.js, npm, @anthropic-ai/claude-code)\n- Workflow configuration (default agent, arguments)\n- Using API key instead\n- Verification\n- Troubleshooting\n\n### 6. **docs/agent-setup-codex.md** (Full contents)\n\nSetup guide for OpenAI Codex including:\n\n- Prerequisites\n- How authentication works (API key-based)\n- Dockerfile requirements\n- Passing the API key via `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV`\n- Workflow configuration (step-level or workflow-level)\n- Fallback chains\n- Verification\n- Troubleshooting\n\n### 7. **docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md** (Full contents)\n\nSystem architecture document covering:\n\n- Overview: Cloche as a grow-coding system\n- System components (three binaries: cloche, cloched, cloche-agent)\n- CLI (`cloche`) responsibilities and subcommands\n- Daemon (`cloched`) responsibilities\n- Agent (`cloche-agent`) responsibilities\n- Communication patterns (gRPC for CLI-daemon, JSON over stdout for agent-daemon)\n- Workflow DSL vocabulary and syntax\n- Hexagonal architecture (domain, ports, adapters)\n- Key interfaces (ContainerRuntime, RunStore, CaptureStore, AgentAdapter, StatusNotifier)\n- Container model (one per run, lifecycle, file extraction via git, security boundaries)\n- Capture system\n- MVP v0.1 scope\n\n### 8. **docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md** (Full contents)\n\nHost workflow design document covering:\n\n- Problem statement: hard-coded orchestration logic\n- Solution: `host.cloche` workflow file with host-side execution\n- New step type: `workflow` (workflow dispatch)\n- Prompt input for workflow steps via `prompt_step`\n- Step output capture to `.cloche/<orch-run-id>/main/<step_name>.out`\n- Environment variables injected into host steps (CLOCHE_TASK_ID, CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR, CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT, CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT)\n- New executor: `HostRunner` in `internal/orchestrator/hostrunner.go`\n- Refactored orchestrator flow\n- Default `host.cloche` template from `cloche init`\n- `.gitignore` updates\n- Safety notes\n- Required code changes\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThe documentation reveals that Cloche is a sophisticated grow-coding platform with:\n\n1. **Three binaries**: CLI client (`cloche`), daemon (`cloched`), and in-container agent (`cloche-agent`)\n2. **Container-isolated workflows** for safe agent execution with network and filesystem controls\n3. **Host workflows** (`.cloche/host.cloche`) for orchestration, enabling extensible multi-phase task pipelines\n4. **DSL-based workflow definition** with steps, results, and wiring for flexible execution graphs\n5. **Three-phase orchestration**: `list-tasks` (discover work) → `main` (execute) → `finalize` (cleanup)\n6. **Multiple agent support**: Claude Code, Codex, or custom commands with fallback chains\n7. **Security-first design**: copy-based isolation, network allowlisting, credential injection, prompt sanitization\n\nHost workflows are the key extensibility point, allowing projects to define custom orchestration strategies beyond the default pull-task → generate-prompt → run-container loop."}],"totalDurationMs":25888,"totalTokens":44401,"totalToolUseCount":10,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3341,"cache_read_input_tokens":39482,"output_tokens":1574,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":3341},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
