[2026-03-13T17:40:09Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XScxd2ztsRjVVnxbUDPP7q","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n## Summary: Host Workflows Implementation\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the codebase, here's how the three host workflows (**list-tasks**, **main**, and **finalize**) are defined, triggered, and operate:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Workflow Definition in `.cloche/host.cloche`**\n\nFile: `/workspace/.cloche/host.cloche`\n\nThe three workflows are defined in a single DSL file:\n\n- **`list-tasks` workflow** (lines 1-9): Discovers available work items. Runs a single step that outputs JSON-formatted task data. Never persisted to the run store (skipped via `SkipRunRecord`).\n\n- **`main` workflow** (lines 11-51): The per-task orchestration loop executed for each open task. Contains steps for:\n  - `claim-task`: Claims an open task \n  - `prepare-prompt`: Generates a prompt for the agent\n  - `develop`: Dispatches a container workflow run\n  - `merge`: Merges results back to main\n  - `cleanup`: Final cleanup step\n\n- **`finalize` workflow** (lines 53-61): Optional post-processing step that runs after `main` completes (success or failure). Receives outcome via environment variables.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Workflow Execution Triggering**\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`** (lines 853-927)\n\nThree-phase orchestration is triggered in the `EnableLoop` method:\n\n1. **Detection** (line 855): `hasWorkflow(hostPath, \"list-tasks\")` checks if host.cloche defines the \"list-tasks\" workflow\n2. **Mode Selection** (lines 855-859):\n   - If \"list-tasks\" exists → creates three-phase loop via `createPhaseLoop()`\n   - Otherwise → falls back to legacy single-function loop via `createLegacyLoop()`\n\n3. **Phase Functions** (lines 879-927):\n   - **listTasksFn** (lines 880-887): Calls `host.RunListTasksWorkflow()` to execute the \"list-tasks\" workflow\n   - **mainFn** (lines 890-899): Calls `runner.RunNamed(ctx, projDir, \"main\")` to execute the \"main\" workflow\n   - **finalizeFn** (lines 902-924): Conditionally created if \"finalize\" workflow exists. Calls `runner.RunNamed(ctx, projDir, \"finalize\")`\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Loop Orchestration Logic**\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go`** (lines 174-271)\n\nThe `runPhased()` method implements the three-phase loop:\n\n```\nPhase 1: list-tasks → discover available tasks\n  ├─ Calls listTasksFn() → returns []Task\n  ├─ Picks first open task not in dedup window\n  └─ Returns task ID or fails over to next poll cycle\n\nPhase 2: main → process task (goroutine per task)\n  ├─ Calls mainFn(ctx, projectDir, taskID)\n  ├─ Blocks until run completes\n  ├─ Tracks run ID in taskRuns map\n  └─ Returns RunResult with state (succeeded/failed)\n\nPhase 3: finalize → cleanup (optional, always runs)\n  ├─ Only if finalizeFn != nil\n  ├─ Calls finalizeFn(ctx, projectDir, taskID, mainResult)\n  ├─ Passes main outcome via ExtraEnv:\n  │  ├─ CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID: ID of the main phase run\n  │  └─ CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME: \"succeeded\" or \"failed\"\n  └─ Runs to completion regardless of main result\n```\n\nConcurrency: `MaxConcurrent` limits how many main/finalize pairs run in parallel. Stagger delays prevent race conditions.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Runner Implementation**\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go`**\n\nKey methods:\n\n- **`Run()`** (lines 41-44): Executes the \"main\" workflow (default entry point)\n- **`RunNamed()`** (lines 51-58): Executes a named workflow (\"list-tasks\", \"main\", or \"finalize\")\n- **`RunListTasksWorkflow()`** (lines 166-183): Special wrapper that:\n  - Sets `SkipRunRecord = true` to avoid cluttering run history\n  - Parses list-tasks output from the last step's `.out` file via `ReadListTasksOutput()`\n  - Returns parsed Task array\n\n- **`runNamedWorkflow()`** (lines 60-164): Core implementation:\n  1. Parses `.cloche/host.cloche` via `dsl.ParseAllForHost()`\n  2. Looks up named workflow in parsed map\n  3. Creates output directory `.cloche/<orchRunID>/output/`\n  4. Creates/updates run record in store (unless `SkipRunRecord` is true)\n  5. Sets up `Executor` with wiring and environment\n  6. Runs workflow via engine and persists final state\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Executor Implementation**\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go`**\n\nThe `Executor` struct (lines 52-64) handles step execution:\n\n- **executeScript()** (lines 92-156): Runs shell commands on the host\n- **executeWorkflow()** (lines 159-221): Dispatches container workflow runs:\n  - Reads prompt from previous step output (or `prompt_step` override)\n  - Calls `Dispatcher.RunWorkflow()` to launch container run\n  - Links child run to parent via `ParentRunID` and `TaskID`\n  - Polls via `waitForRun()` until terminal state\n  - Maps `RunStateSucceeded` → \"success\", others → \"fail\"\n\n- **executeAgent()** (lines 224-278): Runs agent commands on the host\n\nEnvironment variables injected into host steps:\n- `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR`: Project root\n- `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT`: Path to write step output\n- `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT`: Previous step's output file\n- `CLOCHE_RUN_ID`: Host run ID\n- `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`: Assigned task ID\n- `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID`: (finalize only) Run ID from main phase\n- `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME`: (finalize only) Outcome of main phase\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Domain Types**\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go`**\n\n- **StepType** enum (lines 16-20): Includes `StepTypeWorkflow` for workflow dispatch steps\n- **WorkflowLocation** enum (lines 23-33): `LocationHost` vs `LocationContainer`\n- **knownStepConfigKeys** (lines 246-257): Includes:\n  - `workflow_name`: Name of container workflow to dispatch\n  - `prompt_step`: Override which step's output to use as prompt\n\n- **ValidateLocation()** (lines 233-242): Enforces that `workflow_name` steps only appear in host workflows\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`**\n\n- **RunState** constants: `RunStateSucceeded`, `RunStateFailed`, `RunStateCancelled`, `RunStatePending`, `RunStateRunning`\n- **Run.IsHost** flag: True for host workflow runs (set in `runNamedWorkflow()`)\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Parser Implementation**\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go` + tests in `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser_test.go`**\n\n- **ParseAllForHost()** (line 69): Parses `.cloche/host.cloche` and returns `map[string]*domain.Workflow`\n- Supports multiple workflows in same file (list-tasks, main, finalize)\n- Infers `StepTypeWorkflow` when `workflow_name` is present in step config\n- Full test coverage in parser_test.go (lines 650-695)\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Special Handling**\n\n**Task Deduplication** (`/workspace/internal/host/loop.go`, lines 324-346):\n- Prevents reassigning the same task ID within `DedupTimeout` window (default 5 minutes)\n- Dedup entries expire automatically\n\n**Status Tracking** (`/workspace/internal/host/runner.go`, lines 196-256):\n- `hostStatusHandler` logs step events and publishes them via `LogBroadcast`\n- Enables `cloche logs` to work identically for host and container runs\n- Tracks step start/completion times and results\n\n**Daemon Startup** (`/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go`, lines 196-234):\n- `autoRunActiveProjects()` scans projects with `active: true` config\n- Auto-executes host \"main\" workflow at daemon startup (no loop)\n\n---\n\n### 9. **Key Files Summary**\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/workspace/.cloche/host.cloche` | DSL definitions of all three workflows |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go` | Main workflow runner, parses DSL, calls executor |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go` | Step execution (script, agent, workflow dispatch) |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go` | Three-phase orchestration loop, task deduplication, concurrency |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/task.go` | Task structure, JSON parsing, TaskAssigner interface |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` | Loop creation and phase function wiring |\n| `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` | Workflow/step types, location validation |\n| `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` | Daemon startup, auto-run for active projects |"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a26802a4212801954 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 59989\ntool_uses: 23\nduration_ms: 47298</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"832f6df2-1a53-47c0-b762-a9ee0142818b","uuid":"d32fb090-2ded-4863-b46d-33d8d013b2e6","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Search the codebase thoroughly for how host workflows work, specifically looking for references to \"list-tasks\", \"main\", and \"finalize\" workflows. Look in:\n1. internal/host/ directory for workflow executor logic\n2. cmd/cloched/ for daemon code that triggers host workflows\n3. Any workflow DSL parsing code\n4. Any existing .cloche/host.cloche example files\n5. Any constants or special workflow name handling\n\nSearch for these patterns:\n- \"list-tasks\" \n- \"finalize\"\n- \"main\" in context of host workflows\n- HostWorkflow or host workflow types\n- Special workflow names or reserved names\n\nReport back the exact code and file paths showing how these three workflows are defined, triggered, and what they do.","agentId":"a26802a4212801954","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n## Summary: Host Workflows Implementation\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of the codebase, here's how the three host workflows (**list-tasks**, **main**, and **finalize**) are defined, triggered, and operate:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Workflow Definition in `.cloche/host.cloche`**\n\nFile: `/workspace/.cloche/host.cloche`\n\nThe three workflows are defined in a single DSL file:\n\n- **`list-tasks` workflow** (lines 1-9): Discovers available work items. Runs a single step that output